{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <p>Links should be applied when a user needs to jump to content on the same page, visit a page within the same domain, or visit a page within another domain.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/link/when-to-use.svg' | url }}" alt="Link component usage" style="--inline-img-max-width: 752px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4> Content</h4>

  <p>Links are navigational elements, so any text needs to <strong>accurately communicate the destination</strong>. Inconsistent experiences might lead to distrust, lessening the satisfaction of a user during their journey. When writing link content, Inline links should be <strong>descriptive</strong> to help a user better understand the destination whereas Call to action links should be <strong>action-oriented</strong> to entice a user to make a selection.</p>

  <!-- Temporary Warning alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #fdf7e7; border-top: 2px solid #f0ab00; padding: 16px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;"><span style="color:#795600"><strong>Warning</strong></span><br />Link content needs to be written clearly in order to be understood, therefore write <strong>no more than four or five words</strong> per link.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/link/usage-content.svg' | url }}" alt="Link component usage, content" style="--inline-img-max-width: 839px;">
    {%- endcall %}
  </div>

  <h4>Images</h4>

  <div class="margin-top--0 margin-bottom--7">
    <p>Photos or images can be links as long as there is supporting content nearby explaining that a selection can be made, like a headline, content, or Call to action link. Do not hide links in photos or images otherwise a user will miss the opportunity to make a selection if they cannot see the link.</p>
  </div>

  <h4>Buttons</h4>

  <p>Do not apply a link to an action that needs to be triggered instead, like submitting a form or changing a state.</p>

